Name: Memory
Description: Interact with agent memory to store and retrieve information
Share tools: Add Memory, List Memories, Delete Memories
Share Context: memory-context
Metadata: icon: https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@phosphor-icons/core@2/assets/duotone/floppy-disk-duotone.svg
Type: context

#!sys.echo

You have the ability to remember information for the user. Use the Add Memory tool to store important information
that should be remembered. Use List Memories to see what has been stored. Use Delete Memories to clear all stored memories.

---
Name: Add Memory
Description: Store information in agent memory
Param: content: The content to remember

#!${GPTSCRIPT_TOOL_DIR}/bin/gptscript-go-tool add

---
Name: List Memories
Description: List all memories stored for the current agent and thread

#!${GPTSCRIPT_TOOL_DIR}/bin/gptscript-go-tool list

---
Name: Delete Memories
Description: Delete all memories for the current agent and thread

#!${GPTSCRIPT_TOOL_DIR}/bin/gptscript-go-tool delete

---
Name: memory-context
Type: context

#!/bin/bash

MEMORIES=$(${GPTSCRIPT_TOOL_DIR}/bin/gptscript-go-tool list 2>/dev/null)
if [ $? -eq 0 ] && [ -n "$MEMORIES" ]; then
  cat <<EOF
START INSTRUCTIONS: AGENT MEMORIES

Below are memories that have been stored for you to reference:

$MEMORIES

END INSTRUCTIONS: AGENT MEMORIES
EOF
fi
